Eleganza Group has donated some essential materials to support the fight against the dreaded Coronavirus pandemic. These items are 500 diamond armless chairs, 1,152 Eleganza Cares soaps, 9,600 medicated soap, 3,000 big sized cups, 5,000 daily park of bags and 2,000 delight small bags. Eleganza Vice Chairman Mrs Folasade Okoya, said the items were meant for the most vulnerable people in the society. In a statement in Lagos, Mrs. Okoya said: “In this very difficult time of uncertainty, we must all do what we can to ensure the most vulnerable in society are able to get the resources they need. “I am pleased to announce that Eleganza Industrial City Ltd under the Chairmanship of Chief Rasaki Akanni Okoya CON will be making a donation of 50,000pcs essential items, manufactured by our company. “These items will support medical services in an effort to combat the spread of the covid-19 outbreak in Nigeria.”